ce:section.ce:para:
According to the analysis by AFM (Fig. 6
                        ), Table 1
                         summarizes the surface roughness of membranes. Even after embedding pristine UiO-66-NH2 nanoparticles, TFN-U exhibits a similar Rq and Ra as the control TFC membranes because of insufficient compatibility between the polyamide matrix and the unmodified nanoparticles as depicted in Fig. 1. However, after modification by TA, the polyamide layer can adhere to the nanoparticles more closely so the membrane surface fluctuates along with the nanoparticles. Subsequently, the surface roughness of TFN-TU2 and TFN-TU6 becomes higher. For TFN-TU10 and TFN-TU14, as the bulky polymer chains of TA on the nanoparticles fill in the voids between the nanoparticles, the surfaces are flattened again. The effective surface areas of all the membranes are around 40 μm2 per membrane size of 25 μm2 as tabulated in Table 1.
